		   <tr><td valign="top" id="fs8" class="mform2" ><span id="notbold">By:</span> <a href="/db/poster.html?user=145263"><span id=Scholar>lunaticfringesk</span></a><b><span id=Scholar><br>Scholar</span></b><br><img src=/shared/user_star_ico.gif height=9 width=9><img src=/shared/user_star_ico.gif height=9 width=9><br>389 posts
		   <br><nobr><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Decent [2.80]</nobr><br><br /><a href="/cgi-bin/pm.pl?action=addtolist&addname=lunaticfringesk&type=Address" id="fs8"><img src="/shared/plus.gif" border="0" align="middle" height="9" width="9" alt="Add to address book"> Add to address book</a><br /><img src="/shared/transp.gif" width="135" border="0" height="1"></td><td valign="top" class="mform2" width="100%"><p>To be honest, based on your level, you need to get some serious upgrades all over.&nbsp;&nbsp;Items that I noted that I would investigate for possible upgrades are:<br><br>Belt - 16% haste is worthless with SCHW.<br><br>Shield - Although nice, I would upgrade to an AC 25 shield, like Sarnak Battle Shield, for more damage when bashing<br><br>BP - Your legs even have more AC than this thing.  Even a Treeweave would be an upgrade here.<br><br>Serpentine Bracer - Burn this thing  =)<br><br>Mask - Isnt offering you much; look for an upgrade<br><br>I am also guessing that you havent been playing with a 1HS too much; your attack does seem awfully low.  When you max out your skill in 1HS, that should be far higher an amount.<br><br>Noct Blade is a good 1HS weapon.  If you want to play with a 1HB, look into an Ebon Mace, which will outdamage Noct easy, especially at higher levels.<br><br>Based on what you have, I am going to have to disagree with my fellow SKs and their recommendation to switch over to a 2HS (except to keep your skill up).  That would be a mistake.  SKs are tanks and our primary job is to ABSORB damage, NOT DEAL damage.  Granted, dealing damage does play a role, but a far lesser one to absorbing damage.<br><br>Until you reach 1250ish ac, I would almost always wield a shield.  AC is just as important as HP until you reach much higher levels and a shield is the easiest way to crank it up by a significant amount.  <br><br>Further, scroll down a little and you will see a post that I did about dealing damage with a 1H weapon.  Argent Protector will probably outdamage an Noct and a ac25 or greater shield, but it is NOT going to be by leaps and bounds.  1H is clearly your best choice.<br><br>Another advantage of wielding a shield is that you can interrupt spell casting mobs.  Soon you should be fighting more and more mobs that cast spells (like my favorite, SLOW, or another annoying one, Complete Heal../argh).  Wielding a shield gives you the opportunity to interrupt his casting.<br><br>One of the drawbacks of a 1H, and conversely an advantage of a 2H, is spell efficiency.  You dont swing as you are casting.  Therefore, a fast 1H weapon will &quot;miss&quot; swinging far more often than a slower 2H.<br><br>Another advantage of wielding a slower 2H is that it will minimize the damage done by a mob that has a damage shield up (or say, in a PvP environment).<br><br>Also, in general, when studying a 2H to a comparable 1H weapon, the 2H will typically outdamage it.<br><br>However, at the end of the day, 1H, in your situation and based on what I have seen, is clearly the way to go<br><br>Hope this helps<br><br>Luna</p></td></td></tr><tr><td colspan="2" class="mform2"><table border=0 cellspacing=0 cellpadding=0 width="100%"><tr><td id=fs8></td><td align=right id=fs8 >1 Replies</td></tr></table><table width="100%"><tr><td class=mhback>&nbsp;</td><td class=mhback >Thread Subject</a></td><td class=mhback>Started by</a></td><td class=mhback>Replies</a></td><td class=mhback>Last Post</a></td><td class=mhback>Rating</a></td></tr><tr class=mdr>
